<font color="#FF0000">CANNON FODDER</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15 20:44:00 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I've read quite a few books about Nam since coming home.<br>
But only one has had me rolling on the floor laughing.<br>
For that alone I want to thank Phyllis Coleman  <br>
Before Cannon Fodder the subject of Vietnam just held no humor.<br>
As a work of realism the book is a running sore, but as a joke it stands supreme.<br>
The book is clearly written by a low rent wannabe, with a vision of impressing others with his imagined exploits.<br>
Real funny stuff.<br><br>
Just as the war story aspect of the tale rankles us vets... <br>
The sex and sexist parts are sure to irritate the politicly correct. To them I say remember it's all a joke, and Phil Coleman is the only one who doesn't get it. <br><br>
BTY Ed Gentry is only one of Phills fake personas have fun with him. <br>
Happy Trails<br>
Doc<br>
1/22 Inf 1st FF<br><br>
 
